Analysis 1-2: Time analysis of games¶

Q1: What is the average price over the months?¶

In [3]:
steam['release_date'] = pd.to_datetime(steam['release_date'])
steam['year'] = pd.to_datetime(steam['release_date']).dt.year
steam['month'] = pd.to_datetime(steam['release_date']).dt.month
steam['day'] = pd.to_datetime(steam['release_date']).dt.day
steam['year_month'] = pd.to_datetime(steam['year'].astype(str) +'-' + steam['month'].astype(str))
avg_month_steam = steam.groupby('year_month')[['price']].mean().reset_index()

# plot
ggplot(avg_month_steam, aes(x='year_month', y='price')) + \
    geom_point() + geom_line() + \
    labs(x='Month', y='Price') + \
    scale_x_datetime(breaks=date_breaks('1 year'), labels=date_format('%Y')) + \
    ggtitle("Monthly time series of the average price of the games") + \
    theme(figure_size=(14, 7))

Q5: Is there a relationship between positive ratings ratio and the game owner number (estimated number of owners)?¶

In [8]:
pos_own = steam[(steam['positive_ratings']>0) | (steam['negative_ratings']>0)]
pos_own = pos_own[(pos_own['year'] <= 2019) & (pos_own['year'] >= 2005)]
pos_own['positive_ratings_ratio'] = pos_own['positive_ratings']/(pos_own['positive_ratings']+pos_own['negative_ratings'])
estimated_owner = [random.randint(int(i.split('-')[0]),int(i.split('-')[1])) for i in pos_own['owners']]
pos_own['estimated_owner'] = estimated_owner
pos_own = pos_own[(pos_own['estimated_owner']<=10000000) & (pos_own['estimated_owner']>20000)][['positive_ratings_ratio','estimated_owner']]

# plot
sns.set(rc = {'figure.figsize':(12,7)})
sns.set(context='notebook', style='darkgrid', font_scale=1.2)
ax = sns.regplot(x = "positive_ratings_ratio",y = "estimated_owner", data=pos_own,color = 'r', ci = 100)
ax = sns.scatterplot(x = "positive_ratings_ratio",y = "estimated_owner", data=pos_own,color = 'b')
ax.set_title('There exists a positive relationship between positive ratings ratio and the game owner number')

Analysis 7-8: Clustering of games¶

Q7: Are there certain genres of games that have similar ratings?¶

In [11]:
steam_indexed_by_genres = steam.copy()
steam_indexed_by_genres['genres'] = steam_indexed_by_genres['genres'].str.split(';')
steam_indexed_by_genres = steam_indexed_by_genres.explode('genres')
steam_indexed_by_genres = steam_indexed_by_genres.groupby('genres')[['positive_ratings','negative_ratings']].mean()

model = AgglomerativeClustering(distance_threshold=0, n_clusters=None, linkage="complete")
model = model.fit(steam_indexed_by_genres)
steam_indexed_by_genres['cluster'] = model.labels_
In [12]:
def plot_dendrogram(model, **kwargs):
    # Create linkage matrix and then plot the dendrogram

    # create the counts of samples under each node
    counts = np.zeros(model.children_.shape[0])
    n_samples = len(model.labels_)
    for i, merge in enumerate(model.children_):
        current_count = 0
        for child_idx in merge:
            if child_idx < n_samples:
                current_count += 1  # leaf node
            else:
                current_count += counts[child_idx - n_samples]
        counts[i] = current_count

    linkage_matrix = np.column_stack([model.children_, model.distances_,
                                      counts]).astype(float)

    # Plot the corresponding dendrogram
    dendrogram(linkage_matrix, **kwargs,color_threshold=1500)

def plot_dendrogram(model, **kwargs):
    # Create linkage matrix and then plot the dendrogram

    # create the counts of samples under each node
    counts = np.zeros(model.children_.shape[0])
    n_samples = len(model.labels_)
    for i, merge in enumerate(model.children_):
        current_count = 0
        for child_idx in merge:
            if child_idx < n_samples:
                current_count += 1  # leaf node
            else:
                current_count += counts[child_idx - n_samples]
        counts[i] = current_count

    linkage_matrix = np.column_stack([model.children_, model.distances_,
                                      counts]).astype(float)

    # Plot the corresponding dendrogram
#     dendrogram(linkage_matrix, **kwargs)
    dendrogram(linkage_matrix, **kwargs,color_threshold=34)
